Hello! I am a casting director in London looking for a man in his 40s to play a Dealer in a music video shooting on 24th November. 

We are specifically looking for someone who can do card tricks to be the card dealer. A Doug Jones looking character but not necessarily. Could this be you? 

The shoot is set in a poker bar and the plot of the music video is a heist. The pay rate for the Dealer is ¬£200 for the day. 

If you are interested - please email me ASAP with -recent headshot -full name -instagram handle -phone number -email

‚Äî‚Äî > lily.lepage@free.fr

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR NEW PLAY!
--------------------------------

A New Comedic play by Zack Faulks, *Bulimia is My Roman Empire* follows a group of Servants as they attempt to assassinate the Emperor. They discover that power may not be all that they had once desired. Learning that their target is engaged in a number of self-destructive behaviours, our conspirators are forced to follow down a long rabbit hole of strange diets, machismo, and fascism should they want to prove that they deserve the right to rule. As a satire of manhood, ultimately no one‚Äôs happy with where they end up.

For more information check out the images below!

Deadline to submit is Nov. 29, 2025 at 12:00pm.

--------------------
Find us at www.greattrashproductions.ca

**ISO: 15-FT Production Truck Driver (PA)  - Indie Film**

We are seeking a reliable Driver(PA) for our micro-budget indie film.

**Non-Union**

**Location:** Los Angeles Area
**Position:** 15ft Production Truck Driver
**Rate:** $18.19/hour

**Responsibilities:**
* Pick up production truck and deliver to set location
* Return to set after wrap to pick up truck and transport to next location
* Ensure safe and timely transport of production vehicle
* Loading & unloading truck with other assistance

**Work Dates:**
* Thursday, December 4, 2025 (pick up day)
* Friday, December 5, 2025
* Saturday, December 6, 2025
* Sunday, December 7, 2025
* Monday, December 8, 2025
* Tuesday, December 9, 2025
* Friday, December 12, 2025 (potentially - not definite)
* Saturday, December 13, 2025
* Sunday, December 14, 2025
* Monday, December 15, 2025
* Tuesday, December 16, 2025
* Wednesday, December 17, 2025
* Thursday, December 18, 2025 (return day)

**Hours:** These will not be full shooting days. Hours may range from 4 to 6 hours per day as needed for vehicle transport.

**Requirements:**
* Valid driver's license
* Clean driving record
* Experience driving larger vehicles/trucks preferred
* Punctual and dependable

If interested, please submit your resume, a message regarding your interest/experience, and 3 references to info@saltpicturesco.com with your availability and any questions about the position.

As it‚Äôs advertising for alcohol all cast legally need to be at least 25 (production will ask for id to prove this if shortlisted by client) however the concept for the project is quite youthful so max age should be 30. 

Casting Brief: 

Looking for European girls with coloured hair (think red, blue, pink, green, berry, purple) or happy to have their hair coloured for the shoot. 

Looking for European boys with facial hair (a moustache and/or beard - bonus if you have an interesting hair cut too) 

This is a London shoot so looking for London based people only. 

**Shoot Dates: **Thursday 27th + Friday 28th November

Talent to attend both shoot days in London on Location

Based on a 10 hour shoot day including an additional hour for lunch

**Fitting Date:** Monday 24th November, 1-2 hours in London (between 9am and 6pm)

**Talent Age: **All Talent to be over 25 and passport or ID needs to be provided at the time of shortlist to confirm this 

**Talent Rates:**

Talent Day Rates - ¬£600 per person per day

Talent Usage* ¬£5,000 per model

*Usage not guaranteed however all talent are shot in groups so this is very likely to be confirmed

**Talent Wardrobe:**

Talent will be required to bring a couple of outfits to the shoot which will be briefed by the wardrobe stylist

and either brought to the fitting or photographed before the shoot.

¬£50 per person (total not per day)

The deadline is 10AM, Monday 17th November. 

No requests, no PM‚Äôs 

Thank you!

# **üéÑElf Work at Hertfordshire Zoo!üéÑ**

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)
* We have a mixture of performance elf and grotto elf work available

**When You‚Äôll Work:**

The dates we are currently still looking for people are:
* 26th November (4:30pm-8:30pm)
* 29th November (9:30am-4:00pm)
* 30th November (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 6th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 7th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 13th December (9:00am-5:00pm)
* 24th December (9:00am-3:00pm)

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* ¬£14 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If you would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **[entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com](mailto:entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com)**

üî• ATTENTION FILMMAKERS, DIRECTORS & INDIE PRODUCERS üî•

My name is Jerry Valentino Wright ‚Äî published author of 11 books and creator of multiple cinematic universes that are READY to be adapted to film.

I‚Äôm seeking one serious, visionary producer or small production company who sees potential where others see limits ‚Äî someone who wants to help bring a powerful, original franchise to life.

I have several finished books that are visually explosive, emotionally gripping, and built for the screen, including:

üé¨ The Eternal War: Light vs Darkness ‚Äî
A supernatural action-drama with apocalyptic tension, angelic warfare, moral conflict, and a lead character whose destiny shifts the balance between Heaven and Hell.

üé¨ Edge of the Block (series) ‚Äî
Urban, gritty, raw, perfect for a streaming series or limited-run Netflix-style drama.

üé¨ No Mercy Left, The Last Revelation, The Final Prophecy ‚Äî
End-times thrillers with cinematic visuals, spiritual depth, and blockbuster potential.

These aren‚Äôt ‚Äúideas.‚Äù
These are published works, already moving thousands of readers ‚Äî stories built with character arcs, emotional weight, and world-building filmmakers dream about.

I‚Äôm looking for the RIGHT partner:
üëâ A producer with vision
üëâ A director who loves building new worlds
üëâ An indie studio hungry for original IP
üëâ Someone who wants to turn books into films with real impact

If you‚Äôre interested in reading the logline, synopsis, or treatment ‚Äî or if you‚Äôre a filmmaker who loves collaborating with authors ‚Äî comment below or DM me directly.

Let‚Äôs build something legendary.
Let‚Äôs create a film people will feel, not just watch.

‚Äî Jerry Valentino Wright
Author | Creator | Visionary Storyteller

It‚Äôs designed to help you:
 ‚úÖ Let go of what‚Äôs been weighing you down
 ‚úÖ Reconnect to what you truly want
 ‚úÖ Build a plan that actually works for your creative life

If you‚Äôre craving clarity and momentum, this is your sign.
Register here: [https://bit.ly/3LQjWpB](https://bit.ly/3LQjWpB)

DRAMA SHORT FILM CASTING CALL ‚Äì In His Care

SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Red, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother‚Äôs new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Red see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Red. 

Wanted: 1 actors (F) for exciting new short film ‚ÄòIn His Care‚Äô. Shooting in Hertfordshire, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- RED (Female, 24 ‚Äì 30)

- Description: Mid to late 20s

Red is a simple, reserved girl. She is kind and holds herself highly. But when it comes to her grandma, she is extremely protective, fierce even. She is perceptive and head strong and will do anything to find what‚Äôs happening at grandma‚Äôs house.

- Height: 5‚Äô5 ‚Äì 5‚Äô9

- Appearance: Red is a modest girl. She dresses simple when visiting her grandmother, always wearing the infamous red scarf that her grandmother gave her.

- Travel Expenses / Food Paid

please contact sheldonkieran4@gmail.com

items.text:
My name is Jerry Valentino Wright ‚Äî published author of 11 books and creator of multiple cinematic universes that are READY to be adapted to film.

I‚Äôm seeking one serious, visionary producer or small production company who sees potential where others see limits ‚Äî someone who wants to help bring a powerful, original franchise to life.

I have several finished books that are visually explosive, emotionally gripping, and built for the screen, including:

üé¨ The Eternal War: Light vs Darkness ‚Äî
A supernatural action-drama with apocalyptic tension, angelic warfare, moral conflict, and a lead character whose destiny shifts the balance between Heaven and Hell.

üé¨ Edge of the Block (series) ‚Äî
Urban, gritty, raw, perfect for a streaming series or limited-run Netflix-style drama.

üé¨ No Mercy Left, The Last Revelation, The Final Prophecy ‚Äî
End-times thrillers with cinematic visuals, spiritual depth, and blockbuster potential.

These aren‚Äôt ‚Äúideas.‚Äù
These are published works, already moving thousands of readers ‚Äî stories built with character arcs, emotional weight, and world-building filmmakers dream about.

I‚Äôm looking for the RIGHT partner:
üëâ A producer with vision
üëâ A director who loves building new worlds
üëâ An indie studio hungry for original IP
üëâ Someone who wants to turn books into films with real impact

If you‚Äôre interested in reading the logline, synopsis, or treatment ‚Äî or if you‚Äôre a filmmaker who loves collaborating with authors ‚Äî comment below or DM me directly.

Let‚Äôs build something legendary.
Let‚Äôs create a film people will feel, not just watch.

‚Äî Jerry Valentino Wright
Author | Creator | Visionary Storyteller

**Jigsaw Casting is seeking a Weather Reporter for a Quick Serve Restaurant Campaign across Canada**

We are also open to a host or news reporter. They‚Äôre likeable, relatable, charming, and capable of giving an authentic performance. The ideal candidate has real-life reporting experience. The age range is 40s. Someone that knows the weather like the back of their hand, the subtlety and nuances. They‚Äôre confident and engaging, with a comedic sensibility.

This will be filming in Toronto. If someone lives far from this area, travel and accommodation will be provided.

**IF YOU KNOW OF SOMEONE, PLEASE PASS THIS ON!**

This is a non union job. Compensation if selected: $3,075.00. Buyout is based on survival of the edit and includes all lifts, edits, versions.

Must be available for these Important dates:

Recall: Wed Nov 26th, 2025 in Toronto Studio or via zoom if you live far away from Toronto.

Wardrobe: Dec 5th, 2025.

Shoot Date: Dec 9th with a weather hold of Dec 10th, 2025.

*Talent will be shooting outside, in Toronto.

**DEADLINE TO SUBMIT: ASAP OR BEFORE Nov 24th, 2025 AT 11AM EST.**

If interested, you must apply and submit a self tape to:

AUDITION P√Ö ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù I JANUAR üèÜ
S√¶t kryds i kalenderen nu! Audition p√• Nyborg Voldspils n√¶ste store sommermusical under √•ben himmel finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026. Til forestillingen s√∏ges ca. 30 skuespillere, sangere og dansere i alle aldre fra 15 √•r og op til b√•de roller og ensemble. Selve pr√∏veforl√∏bet starter i februar 2026. Der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december 2025 p√• Nyborg Voldspils hjemmeside, hvor man allerede nu kan k√∏be billetter til forestillingen: nyborgvoldspil.dk

ANG√ÖENDE ENSEMBLE, DANS OG KOR: 
Ensemblet medvirker l√∏bende i forestillingen i mange forskellige scener/kostumer og roller/funktioner. Flere fra ensemblet har replik(ker) undervejs. √ònsker man at g√• til audition som danser uden at skulle synge eller have replikker i forestillingen, er dette ogs√• muligt. Inden for dans er ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù en af de musicals med det bredeste felt af genrer, lige fra Las Vegas- og Broadway-showdans til cancan, disco, folkedans, jazzballet, cheerleading og step samt meget mere, og derudover byder koreografierne p√• uendeligt mange komiske indslag og vinkler. Vi gl√¶der os derfor at se mange st√¶rke dansere til audition, uanset om man har erfaring eller ej inden for de individuelle genrer. G√•r man til audition inden for sang og bliver udtaget til koret blandt rollerne/ensemblet, synger man med p√• mange af de 24 numre i forestillingen ud over at indg√• i mange af de komiske indslag og scener undervejs.

ANG√ÖENDE ROLLER:
N√•r der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december, kan man l√¶se alt om de individuelle roller i forestillingen samt hvad man skal forberede, hvis man g√•r op p√• en rolle eller som ensemble. G√•r man op til ensemblet udelukkende som danser (uden at ville synge eller have replikker i forestillingen), vil man ikke skulle forberede noget hjemmefra. 

ANG√ÖENDE FORESTILLINGEN:
G√∏r dig klar til et latter-festbrag uden lige og glem alt, hvad du tror du ved om musicals ‚Äì og riddere! +++ Was erlauben" Constantin? +++
Eine Chronologie sozialer K√§lte

Auch die Mallorca Zeitung berichtet

Kinoproduktion "Der perfekte Urlaub" 

Okt. Nov. 
Auf Mallorca gesuchte Komparsen (√ºberwiegend intern. Touristen) bekommen  82.50 EUR Brutto pro Nachtdreh (bei 5 Drehtagen,10.11.-14.11) je 10 Std. Arbeit + 1Std.Pause
(Abrechnung n. Mindestlohn, Spanien)

6.Nov.
Constantin Film sucht (scheinbar aus der Not) nun auch  kurzfristig aus Deutschland Komparsen incl. √úbernachtungsm√∂glichkeit
 jedoch OHNE Gage, Nachtzulage und  Flugkostenerstattung f√ºr 5 Drehn√§chte
 (s. Online-Gesuch 
(Faire Gagen berichtete)

Nach massiver Kritik vieler Filmschaffender  und auch unser Initiative "Faire Gagen":
Umstrittenes Gesuch wird von Constantin Film kommentarlos gel√∂scht. 

08.Nov.
Constantin Film sucht wiederum in Deutschland Komparsen f√ºr brsagte 5 Drehn√§chte nun  MIT Flugkosten√ºbernahme und 50.00 EUR  Aufwandsentsch√§digung (Gage) diesmal via Agentur Producer's Friend.

"Faire Gagen" fordert dennoch respektvolle Gagen nach dem in Deutschland geltenden gesetzlichen Mindestlohn  einer Nachtzulage und eine  Gleichbehandlung  ALLER  Komparsen am Set via "Offenen Brief" 

"Mallorca Zeitung" (MZ) fragt daraufhin ebenfalls kritisch nach.

Antwort Constantin Film an MZ:  "Die aus Deutschland eingeflogenen Komparsen bekommen selbstverst√§ndlich den in Deutschland √ºblichen Mindestlohn mit Nachtzulage und  auch die Flugkosten-Erstattung (s. Beitrag aus der MZ)

19.Nov. 14.45h
Die Initiative "Faire Gagen" hat trotz Offenen Brief und nochmaliger Bitte, kein Statement und  damit auch keinerlei Erkl√§rung oder Entschuldigung f√ºr die vielen irritierten und ver√§rgerten Filmschaffenden  von Constantin Film erhalten.

Dazu die F√§lle der Vergangenheit bei ebenfalls gro√üen Kinoproduktionen mit den Versuchen bei  hunderten  Komparsen den deutschen Mindestlohn zu umgehen  den wir jedoch ebenfalls durchsetzen konnten.
(Faire Gagen berichtete)

Was bleibt ist ein respektloses Durcheinander mit immer wieder ver√§rgerten, verprellten und verwunderten Komparsen und der Frage: 

"Warum Constantin Film  gerade im eh schon schlecht bezahlten Filmgewerk Komparserie und  Kleindarstellerei wiederholt den  z.T. auch gesetzeswidrigen Rotstift ansetzt?"

+++ Sobald unsere Kritik an die √ñffentlichkeit geht, wird dann schnell alles wie √ºblich ge√§ndert.
Die MZ bekam dann auf eigentlich unsere Kritik und Fragen auch eine Antwort: Darin sind unsere Forderungen pl√∂tzlich "Selbstverst√§ndlich" und "√ºblich".
+++

+++ Die Initiative Faire Gagen und damit  unsere, weiter zunehmende Anh√§ngerschaft, wird diese Einsparversuche auch allgemein keinesfalls mitgehen und weiterhin offen und transparent f√ºr alle Filmschaffenden, den Finger in die Wunde legen. +++

Zudem fordern wir eine Gleichbehandlung der Filmschaffenden am gemeinsamen Set und dulden keine Zweiklassengesellschaft.

Filmschaffende aber auch ganz besonders Filmfans fordern wir auf, genau hinzusehen wenn es um eine verdiente Gage und einen respektvollen Umgang geht.

Auch daher unsere aktuelle Aktion:
H√§nde weg von miesen Gagen.
Siehe Faire Gagen.

+++ Und wie immer die Bitte der Unterst√ºtzung in jeglicher Form unsere wichtigen Beitr√§ge und  unserer aufwendigen und rein ehrenamtlichen Arbeit. Diese lebt nur von Eurer Hilfe, Eurem Engagment und Eurer Wachsamkeit  +++

So haben wir besonders dieses Jahr sehr viel f√ºr uns erreicht und nur so so werden wir gemeinsam auch mit unserern Agenturen respektvolle  Gagen und Zulagen behalten bzw. ausbauen, wo diese noch nicht √ºblich und selbstverst√§ndlich sind.

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

# ***VOCALIST WANTED!***
# ***For: Short film***
# ***'he lives here' ***
## A sleepless corporate worker is forced to confront the monstrous embodiment of their childhood trauma during a terrifying sleep paralysis episode.

A vocalist is needed to compliment the soundtrack for a short film.

Feminine-leaning vocals rooted in harmonising dreamy soundscapes, singing and soft spoken word. 

Inspiration: 

Phoebe Bridgers

Agnes Obel

Ethel Cain 

PLEASE NOTE:

This is a Manchester, UK based opportunity only

Unpaid student film, travel & catering provided

From Writer/Director/Producer Jacob James Ward

[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIponbMURSU)

Send me a DM or message:

jacobward044@gmail.com

items.text:
Hi!

I am an acting teacher living between NYC and Paris and I am so excited to be launching my new acting program in Paris! I have been an acting teacher at the Yale School of Drama for over 13 years & I have brought together some of the most outstanding teachers for our first summer - and there are more to come!

Please spread the word?! 

So many opportunities to train in play, clown, voice and movement, and physical acting this Winter and Spring in NYC & Paris! || 

www.theplaysociety.org

üé¨ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì SOCIAL MEDIA CAMPAIGN (PAID)**
Casting multiple lifestyle roles for a social media video campaign shot in Johannesburg / Pretoria. All roles are paid. Seeking authentic talent with real, natural energy.

üìÖ **Production Date:** Late November 2025 (exact dates TBC)
‚è≥ **Submission Deadline:** ASAP

---

### **ROLES AVAILABLE**

üé≠ **Braai Host (30‚Äì55, any gender)**
Warm, relatable South African energy. Must be comfortable prepping food, handling braai grid/tongs, and interacting naturally in a backyard scene.

üé£ **River Angler (28‚Äì50, any gender)**
Outdoorsy and calm. Should be comfortable mimicking fly-fishing movements and walking on uneven riverbank terrain.

ü•æ **Hiker / Camper (20‚Äì35, any gender)**
Active, capable vibe. Will tie guylines, prep kindling, and perform light camp tasks in a scenic ridge/tent scene.

üöú **Farmer / Farmhand (30‚Äì65, any gender)**

-Non-Union

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew!

Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants that align with the series' message, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

sharedPost.text:
Sharing on behalf of BetweenGigs Casting!!

New Hampshire Casting Call for Union & Non-Union Actors!!

Casting is NOT restricted to New England!! 

Casting for a Sci-Fi trailer.

Casting two actors for a proof-of-concept trailer for an episodic sci-fi thriller. It will be shot at the state of the art Studio Lab facility in Derry NH in mid January. This is a paid gig. Both union and non union talent may submit. A Travel/Lodging budget is available, should talent cast be from outside the New England market.

Please see the details below and submit your materials to casting@humanoriginals.com by end of day Sunday, November 23. Please include contact information for your agent or manager if you have one.

************
Project Title: Resonance: Earth 101
Project Type: Proof-of-Concept Trailer
Union: SAG-AFTRA (Micro-Budget Agreement Pending): Roles are open to both union & non union actors.
Production Company: HumanOriginals
Usage: Online, and client/investor/distributer presentations

Shoot Dates: Two days. Tentatively scheduled for January 13 & 14 2026

Shoot Location: Studio Lab, Derry NH

Fit Date/Table Read: TBD. A stipend will be available
Tech Rehearsal Dates (1-2): TBD. A stipend will be available
Travel Stipend/Lodging: TBD, depending on talent's travel distance.

Shoot/Usage Compensation: $1,000/day per talent.
Meals, credit, and copy will also be provided.

SYNOPSIS
Resonance: Earth 101 is a sci-fi thriller proof-of-concept trailer.

Shortly after crashing on Earth in 1983, Kara discovers a mysterious VHS tape in an abandoned warehouse. This triggers a recorded message from Josh, a Brooklyn teen who seems to know her story, even before they‚Äôve met. Through his nervous humor, warnings about Earth, and a mixtape he calls ‚ÄúEarth 101", Josh offers Kara both survival tools and an unexpected connection.

ROLES
JOSH
‚Ä¢ Male, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A hidden tech prodigy from 1983 Brooklyn ‚Äî sharp, curious, and socially awkward, hiding brilliance behind sarcasm. Nervous yet magnetic. He risks everything to help Kara find her way on Earth.

KARA
‚Ä¢ Female, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A resilient and observant young woman carrying a maturity beyond her years. Athletic and graceful, Kara looks both innocent and ancient, as though she‚Äôs already written into myth. Her arrival on Earth sets off an unexpected chain of events.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS
To be considered for an audition, please email headshot (or current photo), resume, and reel (if available) to casting@humanoriginals.com.

Subject Line of your email should read: Role name / Your name

Submissions are requested by 5:00pm Sunday, November 23. 

If selected to audition, instructions & script for a self-taped audition will be sent to you.

Callbacks, if needed, will be via Zoom.

To be considered for an audition, please email headshot (or current photo), resume, and reel (if available) to casting@humanoriginals.com.

Subject Line of your email should read: Role name / Your name

Submissions are requested by 5:00pm Sunday, November 23. 

If selected to audition, instructions & script for a self-taped audition will be sent to you.

Callbacks, if needed, will be via Zoom.
